               <msContents>
                  <summary>An abridgement in prose and verse of a greater work by <persName key="person_90770167" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90770167/" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Kāshifī, Ḥusayn Vāʻiẓ, d. 1504 or 5 <foreign xml:lang="fa">حسين واعظ كاشفى</foreign>
                     </persName> called <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Rawz̤at al-Shuhadā’ <foreign xml:lang="fa">روضة الشهداء</foreign>
                     </title>, containing the history of Muhammad, Fatimah and the house of Imam ‘All with great emphasis on the afflictions endured by the Imam Husain and those loyal to him at the hand of the infidles. It begins with the first majlis on <locus from="1r" to="1r">1r</locus>, with no title or the preface which is a common practice. The title above given appears on the spine in Latin as Deh Mejalis; it is also given inside the cover in both Latin and Arabic characters, where it is translated into The Ten Assemblies. The divisions of our volume are called majlis, and their arrangement seem to follow more or less the MSS. catalogued by Ethe 10, 160 and 161, and by Rieu BM 155b where the title is given as Dah Majls. However, it contains more than ten majlis with the following headings:</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_146-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6745">Dah Majlis</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_6745">Dah Majālis</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_6745">ده مجلس</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_6745">ده مجالس</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="beginning">مجلس اول در بیان کیفیت وقوع مصیبت کبری و واقعۀ عظمی وفات سید انبیا محمد مصطفی صلی الله علیه و آله از ابن عباس مرویست که چون حضرت رسول صلی الله علیه و آله از حجة الوداع برگشت بآنحضرت معلوم شد که رحلت او بعالم قدس نزدیک شده…</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
